  "output": "Here's the full performance analysis. The frontend is still the Vite default template with nothing real to optimize, so findings are concentrated in the backend.\n\n---\n\n## Performance Analysis\n\n### 1. Database Hit on Every Request (Highest Impact)\n\n**File:** `backend/src/middleware/auth.rs:30`\n\nEvery single request — including high-frequency event ingestion — triggers a `SELECT` against `api_keys`. API keys almost never change; this lookup is a pure waste.\n\n**Fix: in-memory cache with TTL.** Add `moka` (async-ready Rust cache):\n\n```toml\n# Cargo.toml\nmoka = { version = \"0.12\", features = [\"future\"] }\n```\n\n```rust\n// In AppState or passed alongside PgPool\nuse moka::future::Cache;\nuse std::time::Duration;\n\npub type TenantCache = Cache<String, String>; // key_hash -> tenant_id\n\n// In main.rs\nlet tenant_cache: TenantCache = Cache::builder()\n    .max_capacity(1_000)\n    .time_to_live(Duration::from_secs(300))\n    .build();\n```\n\n```rust\n// auth.rs — check cache before hitting DB\nif let Some(tenant_id) = tenant_cache.get(&key_hash).await {\n    req.extensions_mut().insert(Tenant { tenant_id });\n    return Ok(next.run(req).await);\n}\n// ...DB query only on cache miss, then cache.insert(key_hash, tenant_id).await\n```\n\nThis drops auth latency from ~1–5ms (DB round-trip) to microseconds on cache hits.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Missing Database Indexes (High Impact at Scale)\n\n**File:** `backend/migrations/` (wherever your schema is)\n\nThe `events` handler at `events.rs:39` filters by `tenant_id` and orders by `created_at`. Without an index, every GET is a full table scan.\n\n```sql\n-- Add these in a new migration\nCREATE INDEX CONCURRENTLY idx_events_tenant_created\n    ON events (tenant_id, created_at DESC);\n\nCREATE INDEX CONCURRENTLY idx_api_keys_key_hash\n    ON api_keys (key_hash);\n```\n\nThe second index is especially important — it's hit on every auth check.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Connection Pool Too Small\n\n**File:** `backend/src/main.rs:18`\n\n```rust\n.max_connections(5)  // ← this is the current value\n```\n\nWith 5 connections, concurrent event ingestion bursts will queue up waiting for a connection. For a write-heavy analytics platform:\n\n```rust\n.max_connections(20)\n.min_connections(5)\n.acquire_timeout(Duration::from_secs(3))\n```\n\nAlso worth adding `idle_timeout` and `max_lifetime` to prevent stale connections.\n\n---\n\n### 4. No Cursor Pagination on GET /events\n\n**File:** `backend/src/handlers/events.rs:38`\n\nThe hardcoded `LIMIT 100` has no way to page. As events accumulate, there's no way for a frontend to load older data, and returning 100 rows on every call is wasteful if the UI only shows 20.\n\nPattern to add: keyset pagination via `created_at` cursor:\n\n```rust\n// Query parameter: ?before=<ISO timestamp>\n// SELECT ... WHERE tenant_id = $1 AND created_at < $2\n// ORDER BY created_at DESC LIMIT 25\n```\n\nThis is also more performant than `OFFSET`-based pagination because it doesn't require scanning skipped rows.\n\n---\n\n### 5. Redis Not Wired Up\n\n**Stack context:** Your PRD lists Redis, but `Cargo.toml` has no Redis dependency and it's not used anywhere.\n\nBeyond tenant caching (which `moka` handles in-process), Redis becomes valuable for:\n- **Rate limiting** per `tenant_id` (e.g., 10k events/min)\n- **Real-time analytics counters** — increment an event type counter in Redis on each ingest, read from Redis for dashboards instead of aggregating the DB\n- **Write buffering** — batch inserts instead of one `INSERT` per event call\n\nFor Phase 3+ dashboards, querying the DB for `COUNT(*) GROUP BY event_type` per dashboard refresh is expensive. Redis counters are O(1) reads.\n\n---\n\n### 6. SHA-256 Recomputed Per Request\n\n**File:** `backend/src/middleware/auth.rs:26`\n\nMinor, but: SHA-256 is computed on every request before the cache lookup. With caching in place, move the hash computation inside the cache-miss branch so cached hits skip it entirely.\n\n---\n\n### Summary Table\n\n| Issue | File | Impact | Effort |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| DB query per request (auth) | `middleware/auth.rs:30` | High | Low |\n| Missing indexes | migrations | High | Low |\n| Pool size = 5 | `main.rs:18` | Medium | Trivial |\n| No pagination | `handlers/events.rs:38` | Medium | Medium |\n| Redis not wired up | — | Medium (Phase 3) | High |\n| SHA-256 always computed | `middleware/auth.rs:26` | Low | Trivial |\n\n**Frontend:** Nothing to optimize yet — it's the Vite starter template with a counter. Real optimization opportunities will appear once you build the dashboard UI.\n",
